window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Imagine nine women meeting. Tea and cake are on the coffee table. They’ve come together to share their love of books. They are friends. They trust each other. It’s a happy gathering. What could be more harmless? Scratch the surface and look closer. </p> <p>One is lonely, one is desperate and one of them is a killer. </p> <p>When the body of a woman is discovered on a Cambridge common, DCI Barrett and DI Palmer are called to investigate. But the motive behind the crime isn’t clear...and it all leads back to a book club. </p> <p>As the lies, volatile friendships and tension among the group rise to the surface, DCI Barrett and DI Palmer must work out the motive and track down a cold-blooded killer. But just when they think they are on the right track, a twist in the case throws them off course....</p> <p>Betsy Reavley is the best-selling author of multiple thrillers including <i>The Optician's Wife</i>, <i>The Quiet Ones </i>and <i>Frailty</i>. This title is an unmissable new whodunnit which will appeal to fans of authors like Cara Hunter, Rachel Abbott, Faith Martin and LJ Ross.</p>"; 
